        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 25 at 4:28PM PDT until July 25 at 5:00PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>SVRREV

The National Weather Service in Reno has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Placer County in central California...
Nevada County in northern California...
Southern Washoe County in western Nevada...

* Until 500 PM PDT.

* At 428 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Northstar, or
near Tahoe City, moving southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Alpine Meadows, Kings Beach, Tahoe City, Olympic Valley, Northstar,
Carnelian Bay, Incline Village-Crystal Bay, Truckee, Northstar Ski
Area, Homewood, Granite Flat Campground, William Kent Campground,
Ca 89 At Placer-Nevada Co Line, Olympic Valley Ski Area, Dollar
Point, Tahoe State Rec Area Campground, Tahoe Vista, Truckee-Tahoe
Airport, Silver Creek Campground, and Sunnyside-Tahoe City.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
